</P>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- The Cincinnati Bengals released quarterback  
Neil O'Donnell today, two days after drafting Akili Smith of 
Oregon. O'Donnell was released nine months after the Bengals signed 
him to a four-year, $17 million deal. O'Donnell led the Bengals to 
two of their three victories last season. He led Pittsburgh to the 
Super Bowl in 1996. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by SAMANTHA CRITCHELL  
