<HEADLINE> New York Will Fund Jewish Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mayor Rudolph Giuliani appears to have settled a  
dispute over funding for the Museum of Jewish Heritage, announcing 
that the city will pay $22 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Two months ago, Giuliani accused Gov. George Pataki of reneging  
on an agreement to match the city's $11 million contribution. 
Pataki insisted the state had only agreed to provide the land for 
the museum. 
</P>
<P>
	Without fanfare, the mayor released a statement Sunday saying  
the city would fund the entire $22 million. Another $23 million 
needed for the expansion will be raised from private donors. 
</P>
<P>
	The 80,000-square-foot expansion will include a new wing that  
will house a theater, family history center, classrooms and special 
exhibition galleries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
