<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 100; Nasdaq Is Up 16 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up more than  
100 points in the first half-hour of trading. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 3-1 lead over  
decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 16 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up nearly four points. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow tries today to add to its string of five straight record  
closes. 
</P>
<P>
	The blue-chip index rose 320 points last week, although there  
was some weakness in the high-tech arena. 
</P>
<P>
	Corporate earnings news will once again be the main focus for  
the market, with reports this week expected from the likes of 
Microsoft, McDonald's, Procter &AMP; Gamble, IBM and dozens of others. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts say thus far, corporate profits have proven somewhat  
better than had been expected, with very few negative surprises. 

</P>
</TEXT>
