<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 11:10 a.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow Up Nearly 200  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is on track for  
a sixth straight record today as blue-chips were helped by strong 
earnings reports and merger news. But technology shares backed off 
a strong opening despite gains at Compaq Computer following a 
surprise weekend management shakeup. Just before 11 a.m. EDT, the 
Dow industrials were up 186.76 at 10,680.65. Gainers on the New 
York Stock Exchange led losers 1,949-668. The Nasdaq was down 1.02 
at 2,483.02. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures just before 11 a.m. EDT:  
