<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Farmers Insurance Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SIOUX FALLS, S.D. (AP) -- In an April 8 story about farmers  
dropping their health insurance, The Associated Press erroneously 
reported that self-employed people may deduct 60 percent of their 
medical costs on their 1999 and 2000 taxes. 
</P>
<P>
	Under federal legislation signed in October, the self-employed  
may deduct 60 percent of their health insurance premiums for 1999 
through 2001. 
</P>
