<HEADLINE> Heat's Askins suspended one game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Keith Askins of the Miami Heat was fined $5,000 and suspended for one game by the  
NBA Monday for his actions in Sunday's game against Indiana. 
<P>
	Askins committed a flagrant foul, elbowing Antonio Davis of the  
Pacers with 10:49 to play in the Heat's 92-88 victory. He was 
suspended for Monday night's game at Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
	The league also fined Vancouver's Cherokee Parks $5,000 for  
making an obscene gesture during the Grizzlies' 89-75 loss at 
Minnesota last Friday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
