<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brewers Put Pulsipher on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- The Milwaukee Brewers placed pitcher Bill  
Pulsipher on the 15-day disabled list Monday, retroactive to 
Saturday, because of a lower back strain. 
</P>
<P>
	``Fifteen days should be fine for him,'' manager Phil Garner  
said. ``I don't anticipate that to be a problem. He's a maximum 
effort-type guy. He hits the ground hard when he comes off the 
mound and it hurts his back.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Pulsipher was 1-1 with a 6.75 ERA in two starts. He was  
scheduled to start Wednesday against St. Louis; Rafael Roque will 
pitch in his place. 
</P>
<P>
	Taking Pulsipher's spot on the roster is right-hander Steve  
Falteisek, whose contract was purchased from Triple-A Louisville. 
</P>
<P>
	``We want to use him and he's ready to go,'' Garner said of his  
new reliever. ``He has a heavy sinker and a hard slider. If he 
throws strikes, he'll be extremely successful.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Pulsipher had back surgery during the off-season. The back  
problem was aggravated during his last start against the Cubs in 
the home opener last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Falteisek was 1-1 with a 2.89 ERA in five relief appearances at  
Louisville. In 1997, he was 0-0 with a 3.38 ERA in five games for 
Montreal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
