<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pincay Wins Twice at Santa Anita </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Laffit Pincay, within striking range of  
Bill Shoemaker's record of 8,833 career riding victories, was 
aboard two winners Monday including the feature race on closing day 
of Santa Anita's winter-spring meeting. 
</P>
<P>
	Pincay rode Enjoy The Moment to a half-length triumph over  
Champ's Star in the $107,900 Valiant Pete Handicap. Pincay was also 
aboard the winner in the 10th and final race of the day, putting 
him at 8,731 career wins -- 102 behind Shoemaker's record. 
</P>
<P>
	Pincay rode at least one winner on the final nine days of the  
Santa Anita meeting and wound up third in the jockey standings. 
</P>
<P>
	``I should be leading rider,'' Pincay said. ``I'm a senior  
citizen -- 52 years old -- so I should get 20 winners before the meet 
starts, like a golf handicap. If they had, I probably would have 
ended up leading rider.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That honor went to David Flores, who led his first major race  
meeting with 75 victories. Alex Solis finished second with 65 wins 
while Pincay had 58. 
</P>
<P>
	Enjoy The Moment, who carried 117 pounds, beat males in the  
Valiant Pete race, covering six furlongs in 1:08 4-5. The 
4-year-old daughter of Slew's Royalty was the 5-2 favorite and paid 
$7.20, $4.20 and $3.40. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the seventh in 12 lifetime starts for Enjoy The  
Moment and was worth $64,740, raising her career earnings to 
$301,520. 
</P>
<P>
	Champ's Star returned $6.20 and $4.40. Peach Flat paid $5.40 to  
show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
