<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Nasdaq Falls 138.19; Dow Off 53.36  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A fierce selloff in technology shares this  
afternoon pounded the Nasdaq composite index down 5.6 percent and 
more than erased a 270-point gain in the Dow Jones industrials. The 
technology heavy Nasdaq composite fell 138.19 points to 2,345.85. 
The only time the index had a steeper one-day point drop was the 
140.43-point pummeling of Aug. 31, 1998, a slide of 8.6 percent. 
The Dow Jones industrial average ended a five-day string of record 
highs, falling 53.36 to close at 10,440.53. At early afternoon, the 
Dow had surged up 271.85 points to reach 10,765.74. On the NYSE, 
advancers led decliners 1,933-1,195. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
