<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Three Tenors Perform in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PRETORIA, South Africa (AP) -- The Three Tenors have conquered  
another corner of the globe. 
</P>
<P>
	Some 35,000 music lovers were on hand Sunday as Jose Carreras  
led off the trio's first African concert with the bittersweet 
``Lamento die Federico'' from Cilea's ``L'arlesiana.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Despair rang deep through Placido Domingo's rendition of ``E  
lucevan le stelle'' from Puccini's opera ``Tosca.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But the effusive Luciano Pavarotti, the spirit behind the group  
that started performing nine years ago in Rome, held the heart of 
the audience. 
</P>
<P>
	``Pavarotti was magnificent, perfecto,'' said John Motsa, 23.  
</P>
<P>
	The main concert backer, Vodacom, intended the concert to  
celebrate the first five years of democracy in South Africa. The 
performance was held on the sloping lawn at the Union Buildings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
