<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Baseball Quizzes Darryl Strawberry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Major league baseball interrogated troubled New  
York Yankees outfielder Darryl Strawberry for several hours on 
Sunday about his latest arrest, according to a published report. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to the questioning by baseball and players union  
officials, Strawberry was also given another drug test, the New 
York Daily News reported today, citing multiple sources. 
</P>
<P>
	Though Yankees general manager Brian Cashman told the newspaper  
he had no knowledge of Strawberry's meeting with baseball 
officials, the Daily News also reported that the results of a drug 
test taken by Strawberry on Tuesday in Tampa, Fla., was to be made 
available to the team today. 
</P>
<P>
	If Strawberry's drug tests were to come back clean, baseball is  
unlikely to take any action against the outfielder until the 
criminal charges of his arrest are resolved, a source familiar with 
Sunday's hearing told the newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry intends to plead not guilty to the charges of cocaine  
possession and solicitation for prostitution leveled against him as 
a result of Wednesday night's arrest, according to his Tampa 
attorney, Joseph Ficarrotta. 
</P>
<P>
	In the meantime, Strawberry has not been permitted to work out  
at the Yankees' complex in Tampa, where he has been while 
completing his chemotherapy treatments after colon cancer surgery. 
Also, the team has stopped payments of his $2.5 million salary. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry reportedly returned to Tampa after the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
