<HEADLINE> Solutia To Buy CPFilms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Solutia Inc. will buy CPFilms Inc., a maker of  
specialty film, from Akzo Nobel N.V. for $200 million. 
</P>
<P>
	CPFilms is the world market leader in window film and other film  
products for automotive and architectural uses. The business has 
sales of about $130 million annually. 
</P>
<P>
	CPFilms employs about 640 people, mostly in Virginia, suburban  
Los Angeles, and the United Kingdom. No layoffs are expected, a 
Solutia spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
	CPFilms will become part of Solutia's Saflex division. Saflex  
plastic interlayer, one of Solutia's leading products, is used to 
make laminated glass for automotive and architectural applications. 
</P>
<P>
	Solutia, an applied chemistry company, was spun off in 1997 from  
Monsanto Co. Solutia had sales of $3 billion in 1998, and employs 
8,700 workers worldwide. 

</P>
</TEXT>
