<HEADLINE> Hungarian Leader, Clinton To Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will play host to Hungarian  
President Arpad Goncz for a state visit from June 7 to June 9, the 
White House announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``The visit will celebrate Hungary's long struggle for freedom,  
democracy and human rights,'' White House press secretary Joe 
Lockhart said in a prepared statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Goncz was jailed for six years for his role in the 1956  
Hungarian revolution. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton and his Hungarian counterpart were expected to discuss  
Hungary's role as a new member of in NATO and the crisis in Kosovo. 
</P>
